14/01/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis urged all Greek scientists living and working abroad to return to Greece on Thursday (13 January).
The open invitation came after the first meeting of the newly established National Council for Research and Technology, which was formed to support and improve development of education and science in the country.
Karamanlis said government goals depend on economic competitiveness, productivity of both the public and private sectors, and most importantly, the ability to make scientific breakthroughs.
(ANA - 13/01/05)
